[event] -> {"id":"chatcmpl-bfd1db14-7011-4498-adfc-d820783f8268","object":"chat.completion.chunk","created":1774367664,"model":"groq/compound-mini","system_fingerprint":null,"choices":[{"index":0,"delta":{"executed_tools":[{"index":0,"type":"search","arguments":"{\"query\": \"Groq AI models for coding\"}","output":"Title: Coding with Groq - GroqDocs\nURL: https://console.groq.com/docs/coding-with-groq\nContent: Login\n\nLog In\n\n# Coding with Groq\n\nUse Groq's fast inference in your favorite coding tools.\n\n## Most Popular\n\n### Factory Droid\n\nAutonomous engineering agent from Factory.ai that pairs planning, implementation, and review with Groq's low-latency inference.### OpenCode\n\nOpen-source AI coding agent available as a terminal-based interface, desktop app, or IDE extension with native Groq support.\n\n## More Tools\n\nKilo Code\n\nAI-powered coding assistant for VS Code, Cursor, and JetBrains with native Groq provider support.Roo Code\n\nAI-powered coding assistant for VS Code with native Groq provider support.Cline\n\nAI coding assistant for VS Code, Cursor, JetBrains, and CLI with native Groq support.\n\n## Recommended Models\n\n`moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905`\nMost Popular [...] `moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905`\nMost Popular\n\nMoonshot AI— Advanced reasoning with 256K context windowOpenAI— Powerful open-source model for complex coding tasksExplore all available models in the Groq model catalog\n\n### Was this page helpful?\n\n#### On this page\nScore: 0.8269\n\nTitle: Unlocking the Power of Groq's LLM with LangChain - Medium\nURL: https://medium.com/@priyanka_neogi/unlocking-the-power-of-groqs-llm-with-langchain-f29e926bf406\nContent: ## Summary: The Seven Steps to AI-Powered Code Generation\n\n1. Import libraries to connect to Groq and LangChain.\n2. Set your API key to authenticate with Groq’s servers.\n3. Initialize the model you want to use (e.g., LLaMA 3).\n4. Define a prompt template with placeholders for flexible questions.\n5. Create an LLMChain that connects the model and the prompt.\n6. Run the chain with your specific task details.\n7. Print or use the generated output in your application.\n\n## Final Thoughts\n\nIntegrating Groq’s AI models with LangChain opens a world of possibilities for automating complex language tasks. Whether you want to generate code, create custom chatbots, or automate text generation, this approach makes it straightforward and scalable. [...] Sitemap\n\nOpen in app\n\nSign in\n\nSign in\n\n# Unlocking the Power of Groq’s LLM with LangChain\n\nPriyanka Neogi\n\nPriyanka Neogi\n\n5 min readMay 22, 2025\n\nPress enter or click to view image in full size\n\nThe rapid advancement of large language models (LLMs) has transformed how developers interact with AI. Instead of hardcoding every function or task, you can now leverage powerful AI models to generate code snippets, answer questions, or even build entire applications on the fly.\n\nToday, I’m going to walk you through a simple yet effective example that integrates Groq’s LLM with the LangChain framework to automatically generate Python code for any given programming task. [...] Technical details:  \nThe `result` is a dictionary containing the model’s output under the key `\"text\"`. This line prints the generated code snippet to the console.\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nThis simple yet elegant integration shows how to build AI-powered code generation tools with minimal effort. You can expand this framework to create chatbots, question-answering systems, or intelligent assistants that understand your custom instructions.\n\nThe beauty of LangChain is its abstraction — no need to manually format API calls or parse raw outputs. And Groq’s powerful LLM models provide high-quality responses with impressive speed.\n\n## Summary: The Seven Steps to AI-Powered Code Generation\nScore: 0.7964\n\nTitle: Supported Models - GroqDocs\nURL: https://console.groq.com/docs/models\nContent: Login\n\nLog In\n\n# Supported Models\n\nExplore all available models on GroqCloud.\n\n## Featured Models and Systems\n\n### Groq Compound\n\nGroq Compound is an AI system powered by openly available models that intelligently and selectively uses built-in tools to answer user queries, including web search and code execution.\n\nToken Speed\n\n~450 tps\n\nModalities\n\nCapabilities### OpenAI GPT-OSS 120B\n\nGPT-OSS 120B is OpenAI's flagship open-weight language model with 120 billion parameters, built in browser search and code execution, and reasoning capabilities.\n\nToken Speed\n\n~500 tps\n\nModalities\n\nCapabilities\n\n## Production Models\n\nNote: Production models are intended for use in your production environments. They meet or exceed our high standards for speed, quality, and reliability. Read more here. [...] ## Production Systems\n\nSystems are a collection of models and tools that work together to answer a user query.\n\n  \n\n| MODEL ID | SPEED (T/SEC) | PRICE PER 1M TOKENS | RATE LIMITS (DEVELOPER PLAN) | CONTEXT WINDOW (TOKENS) | MAX COMPLETION TOKENS | MAX FILE SIZE |\n ---  ---  --- \n| Compoundgroq/compound | 450  200K TPM200 RPM | 131,072 | 8,192 \n| Compound Minigroq/compound-mini | 450  200K TPM200 RPM | 131,072 | 8,192 \n\n  \n Learn More About Agentic Tooling\n\nDiscover how to build powerful applications with real-time web search and code execution\n\n## Preview Models\n\nNote: Preview models are intended for evaluation purposes only and should not be used in production environments as they may be discontinued at short notice. Read more about deprecations here. [...] | MODEL ID | SPEED (T/SEC) | PRICE PER 1M TOKENS | RATE LIMITS (DEVELOPER PLAN) | CONTEXT WINDOW (TOKENS) | MAX COMPLETION TOKENS | MAX FILE SIZE |\n ---  ---  --- \n| Canopy Labs Orpheus Arabic Saudicanopylabs/orpheus-arabic-saudi  $40.00 per 1M characters | 50K TPM250 RPM | 4,000 | 50,000 \n| Canopy Labs Orpheus V1 Englishcanopylabs/orpheus-v1-english  $22.00 per 1M characters | 50K TPM250 RPM | 4,000 | 50,000 \n| Llama 4 Scout 17B 16Emeta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct | 750 | $0.11 input$0.34 output | 300K TPM1K RPM | 131,072 | 8,192 | 20 MB |\n| Llama Prompt Guard 2 22Mmeta-llama/llama-prompt-guard-2-22m  $0.03 input$0.03 output | 30K TPM100 RPM |  | 512 \n| Prompt Guard 2 86Mmeta-llama/llama-prompt-guard-2-86m  $0.04 input$0.04 output | 30K TPM100 RPM | 512 | 512\nScore: 0.7871\n\nTitle: Groq Provider - AI SDK\nURL: https://ai-sdk.dev/v5/providers/ai-sdk-providers/groq\nContent: `gemma2-9b-it`\n`llama-3.1-8b-instant`\n`llama-3.3-70b-versatile`\n`meta-llama/llama-guard-4-12b`\n`deepseek-r1-distill-llama-70b`\n`meta-llama/llama-4-maverick-17b-128e-instruct`\n`meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct`\n`meta-llama/llama-prompt-guard-2-22m`\n`meta-llama/llama-prompt-guard-2-86m`\n`moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905`\n`qwen/qwen3-32b`\n`llama-guard-3-8b`\n`llama3-70b-8192`\n`llama3-8b-8192`\n`mixtral-8x7b-32768`\n`qwen-qwq-32b`\n`qwen-2.5-32b`\n`deepseek-r1-distill-qwen-32b`\n`openai/gpt-oss-20b`\n`openai/gpt-oss-120b`\n\nThe tables above list the most commonly used models. Please see the Groq\ndocs for a complete list of available\nmodels. You can also pass any available provider model ID as a string if\nneeded.\n\n## Browser Search Tool [...] `gemma2-9b-it`\n`1\n\nconst model = groq('gemma2-9b-it');`\n\n### Reasoning Models\n\nGroq offers several reasoning models such as `qwen-qwq-32b` and `deepseek-r1-distill-llama-70b`.\nYou can configure how the reasoning is exposed in the generated text by using the `reasoningFormat` option.\nIt supports the options `parsed`, `hidden`, and `raw`.\n\n`qwen-qwq-32b`\n`deepseek-r1-distill-llama-70b`\n`reasoningFormat`\n`parsed`\n`hidden`\n`raw`\n`1\n\nimport { groq } from '@ai-sdk/groq';\n\n2\n\nimport { generateText } from 'ai';\n\n3\n\n4\n\nconst result = await generateText({\n\n5\n\nmodel: groq('qwen/qwen3-32b'),\n\n6\n\nproviderOptions: {\n\n7\n\ngroq: {\n\n8\n\nreasoningFormat: 'parsed',\n\n9\n\nreasoningEffort: 'default',\n\n10\n\nparallelToolCalls: true, // Enable parallel function calling (default: true)\n\n11 [...] 11\n\nuser: 'user-123', // Unique identifier for end-user (optional)\n\n12\n\nserviceTier: 'flex', // Use flex tier for higher throughput (optional)\n\n13\n\n},\n\n14\n\n},\n\n15\n\nprompt: 'How many \"r\"s are in the word \"strawberry\"?',\n\n16\n\n});`\n\nThe following optional provider options are available for Groq language models:\n\nreasoningFormat 'parsed' | 'raw' | 'hidden'\n\nControls how reasoning is exposed in the generated text. Only supported by reasoning models like `qwen-qwq-32b` and `deepseek-r1-distill-` models.\n\n`qwen-qwq-32b`\n`deepseek-r1-distill-`\n\nFor a complete list of reasoning models and their capabilities, see Groq's reasoning models documentation.\n\nreasoningEffort 'low' | 'meduim' | 'high' | 'none' | 'default'\n\nControls the level of effort the model will put into reasoning.\nScore: 0.7628\n\nTitle: GROQ | aider\nURL: https://aider.chat/docs/llms/groq.html\nContent: Groq currently offers free API access to the models they host. The Llama 3 70B model works well with aider and is comparable to GPT-3.5 in code editing\nScore: 0.7501\n\nTitle: Meet Groq: Making Large Language Models Lightning-Fast\nURL: https://medium.com/@okanyenigun/meet-groq-making-large-language-models-lightning-fast-0f8a885073b9\nContent: attractive solution for applications such as smart cities, autonomous vehicles, and IoT devices.8. Industrial-grade: Groq's technology is designed to meet the demands of industrial-grade AI applications, where reliability, scalability, and performance are critical. This makes it an attractive solution for industries such as manufacturing, energy, and healthcare.Overall, Groq's innovative technology has the potential to significantly accelerate the development and deployment of AI models, enabling new applications and use cases that were previously impractical or impossible.\"\"\" [...] vision, natural language processing, and reinforcement learning. T